REPLACE INTO `html` (`Section`, `Date`, `Title`, `Content`) VALUES 
('credits', '2008-01-25 00:00:00', '', '<ul>\r\n<li><span>Lukáš Čajági</span> - author of our fantasy novels</li>\r\n<li><span>Cassiraa</span> - design and new features ideas</li>\r\n<li><span>Igniteice</span> - balance changes and new cards suggestions</li>\r\n<li><span>Sylonus</span> - new game mechanics and new cards suggestions</li>\r\n<li><span>Viperio</span> - balance changes and new cards suggestions</li>\r\n<li><span><a href="http://www.x-factor.tym.sk">X-Factor</a></span> - images refinement (cards and others), new card images design</li>\r\n</ul>'),
('faq', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '<h4>Q1: I have noticed some unexpected behaviour from the system, I think I have found a bug. What should I do now?</h4>\r\n<p>A: Go trough F.A.Q. first and if you can''t find your answer there please document the bug (screenshot, page source) and send it to either <a href="mailto:illuminati@pobox.sk">Mojko</a> or <a href="mailto:theultramage@gmail.com">theultramage</a>. In the e-mail, try to describe the bug itself, then the circumstances in which the bug appeared. Another option is to use our bug tracking system at <a href="https://netvor.sk/trac/arcomage">https://netvor.sk/trac/arcomage</a>. We will do what we can to solve the problem.</p>\r\n<h4>Q2: I can''t log in. How do I fix that?</h4>\r\n<p>A: If you are sure you have used the right login and password, try to delete cookies for our site in your browser. You should find cookie management in options/preferences/advanced options.</p>\r\n<h4>Q3: My browser doesn''t display your site properly. You have errors in your website. Can you fix it?</h4>\r\n<p>A: We made this website according to <a href="http://www.w3.org/">W3C</a> standards, so the cause is most likely the browser you''re using. We know that IE7, <a href="http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/firefox/?from=getfirefox">Firefox</a> and <a href="http://www.opera.com/">Opera</a> have no problems displaying it, perhaps you could try using one. Writing a report might not be a bad idea, too - it would help us make future plans.</p>\r\n<h4>Q4: When I play a card, its cost should be subtracted from my stock, but it isn''t. I ended up with more resources than I should have. Why is that?</h4>\r\n<p>A: The card cost is always the same as it is displayed on the card. There is no way these two values would differ. So you probably didn''t realize that after the card is played (at the end of your turn), you get resources from your facilities. This is probably the reason why you ended up with more resources than you expected.</p>\r\n<h4>Q5: What is a turn anyway? How it works?</h4>\r\n<p>A: Turn is one elementary step in a game you are playing. A turn consits of these steps:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Cost of a card is substracted</li>\r\n	<li>Effect of the card takes place</li>\r\n	<li>Keywords with side-effects apply</li>\r\n	<li>Resource production</li>\r\n	<li>Game limits apply (resources cannot be lower then 0, wall below 0, facitlies below 1...)</li>\r\n	<li>End game condition is checked</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h4>Q6: I played an if-then-else card, fulfilling the condition, but instead the secondary effect took place. Why?</h4>\r\n<p>A: Remember that this condition is evaluated AFTER the card cost is subtracted from your stock. This may be the reason why the secondary effect was chosen.</p>\r\n<h4>Q7: I played a "Swift" card and I got an unexpected increase of resources. How does a "Swift" card work?</h4>\r\n<p>A: Simple - by playing a "Swift" card you get a full extra turn, including resource production.</p>\r\n<h4>Q8: Is the number of "Swift"/"Quick" cards played in a row limited?</h4>\r\n<p>A: No. You can make arbitrarily long chains of "Swift"/"Quick" cards.</p>\r\n<h4>Q9: I used F5 to refresh the game and for some reason a card was played by itself.</h4>\r\n<p>A: Use OUR refresh button (located on the upper right part of the screen), not the one on the browser. For quick access use shorcut ALT+w.</p>\r\n<h4>Q10: I played a card ("Master of past" for example) that reverses or undos some effect of opponents last played card and it didn''t work like it should have.</h4>\r\n<p>A: You probably played such card after "Swift"/"Quick" card(s). So when you played it, the system no longer had the information what effect was caused by opponent''s last turn. There is an easy rule for these cards - if you want them to work fine, don''t play them after any "Swift"/"Quick" cards.</p>\r\n<h4>Q11: Some cards have "recently discarded cards" in their effect. What does that mean?</h4>\r\n<p>A: Recently discarded cards are following cards:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Card discarded by you with discard button last turn</li>\r\n	<li>Cards that were discarded by you last turn by some card effect</li>\r\n	<li>Cards that were discarded by opponent last turn by some card effect</li>\r\n</ul>'),
('help', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '<p>\r\nArcomage is a fantasy turn-based card game.\r\nThis card game simulates an epic battle between two empires including features such as constructing new buildings, training troops and decimating the enemy empire with standard attacks or sneaky tactics such as intigue or spells.\r\nMArcomage is its online version for two human players.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Overview</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n<a style="float: right;" href="img/screen_start_game.png"><img src="img/screen_start_game_s.png" alt="start game screen"/></a>\r\nThe game consists of turns. In one turn a player can play one card. Then the next turn follows, where the other player can play cards.\r\nThis way the players play the game - always one playing cards and the other one waiting for the next turn where he can play cards.\r\nThe cards themselves modify some attributes of the game (such as tower and wall height, resources ...).\r\nThe game is very simple and easy to operate. There is much information on the game screen, we will now describe some basic information, in the picture to the right. In the upper left of the screen, your login name is written. In the upper part you can see the navigation bar, which is used to travel between sections. Right below the navigation bar you can see the round indicator, that keeps you informed in which round the game currently is. In the center-left part there is a game list manager. You can use it to jump to another game or you can traverse trough games, in which your turn is, via "Next game" button. In the center of the screen you can see card history. There are no cards there yet, but later it will hold the card(s) recently played by you and your opponent. Above card history is the notice which informs you which player''s turn currently is. Furthermore if opponent''s name is colored white it means that he is currently on-line. When waiting for opponent''s turn, you need to refresh the game with our refresh button.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For practice you can <a href="http://www.x-factor.tym.sk/Arcomage/Arcomage.rar">download</a> and play single player Arcomage to learn the basics.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Game attributes: Resources, facilities, resource production, tower and wall</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n<a style="float: right;" href="img/screen_resources.png"><img src="img/screen_resources_s.png" alt="resources"/></a>\r\nEvery player has three types of resources: Bricks, Gems and Recruits, and three types of resource production facilities: Quarry, Magic and Dungeon (generating resources in the corresponding order).\r\nBricks are the basic building material, used mostly for constructing buildings.\r\nMagic powered soul gems (shortly gems) represent the magical power at your disposal.\r\nAnd finally, recruits represent your living or fighting power (ammount of creatures, soldiers and weapons).\r\nAt the end of turn, for each facility of certain type, one resource of the corresponding type is added to the active player''s stock.\r\nExample: If Quarry = 3, at the end of turn, three Bricks will be added to the stock.\r\nThe number of facilities of any kind cannot drop below one, and the ammount of a resource of a certain type cannot be lower than zero. In the picture you can see where resources and facilities info is displayed. Your resources and facilities are to the left and opponent''s  are to the right. Every player has his/her own tower and wall, each having a height. Tower height can be at most 100, wall has height limit 150. In the case of a standard enemy attack, the attack will first lower the wall. Only after the wall height is zero and some attack power still remains will the tower be lowered. Example: Enemy attacks with an attack power of 25, wall height is 10, tower height is 20. After the attack, the wall height will be zero and the tower height will be 5. There are some cards that do damage to the tower directly, bypassing the wall. Tower and wall information are located in the bottom-left part (yours) and bottom-right (opponent''s). Moreover, if some of these game attributes were changed due to effect of some card, it will be indicated. When the game attribute was increased, it will be highlighted with limegreen color, if it was decreased in will be highlighted in orange color.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Victory types</h4>			\r\n<p>\r\nThe goal of the game is to defeat your opponent by reaching one or more victory conditions.\r\nThe following outcomes are possible:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>tower destruction</b><br/>\r\nRaze the enemy tower to the ground to win - meaning, lower the enemy tower to zero height. Usually achieved by green cards and standard attacks.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>tower building</b><br/>\r\nBuild up your tower to height 100 to win. Usually achieved by delaying enemy attacks while building your tower.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>resource accumulation</b><br/>\r\nAccumulate 400 of resources (total sum) to win. Beware of cards that cripple your stock.\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<b>timeout</b><br/>\r\nEach game is limited to 250 rounds. Afterwards, both players'' states are compared (in the order: tower, wall, no. of facilities, sum of resources). Whoever has more (in that order), wins. Otherwise the game is declared a draw.\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\nSpecial rules apply in the case where both players achieve a victory condition simultaneously.\r\n<br/>\r\nIf the victory type for both is the same, the result is, logically, a draw.\r\n<br/>\r\nIf the victory types are different, the following rule is used to determine the winner:\r\nDestruction victory > Tower bulding victory > Resource victory > Timeout victory.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>After the game is finished and a player leaves the game, his opponent is informed about this with "player has left the game" message in the chat window.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Cards</h4>\r\n<p><img style="float: right" src="img/screen_card.png" alt="card"/>Every card has a name, a price and an effect. The name and the price are found in the upper part of the card, the effect in the lower part, below the card picture. The price is the ammount of resources needed for a card to be played, each type of resource represented by the color related to the resource. This ammount will be subtracted from the resource stock when the card is played. The card can only be played if you have enough resources to pay for its price. After a card is played, its effect will take place. Every card belongs to some group, indicated by the card''s border color. There are three groups: Common, Uncommon and Rare. Common cards have green border, Uncommon brown and Rare yellow. Every player has exactly eight cards in his or hers hand. Your cards are located at the upper part of the screen. Opponent''s cards are located in the bottom part of the screen. You can see enemy''s cards in his or hers hand. Some cards in yours/opponent''s hand are marked with "New card" flag. This indicates that this card has been received to the hand only recently. You may want to pay close attention to these cards. In the middle of the game screen are cards last played by each player (it can be very important). In one turn one player plays one card (more if played card says so) or a player can discard a card instead of playing it. When a card is discarded, its cost is not payed, but its effect will not happen. After a card(s) has been played or discarded a new card(s) will be added to player''s hand. The new card will be chosen randomly from the card groups with probabilities 65% for Common, 29% for Uncommon and 6% for Rare, unless a played card says otherwise. Some cards have modes. If a card has more modes, it means it can be played with different effects. The effects are described on the card. For example card Merchant will add 6 bricks, when played in Mode1, 5 gems when played in Mode2 or 5 recruits, when played in mode3. When you can play such card, there is a mode selector next to the play button. Simply select the chosen mode of the card and play it. Some cards discard other cards from yours or opponents hand. Cards that where discarded during your last turn(s) are located to the left of the card history. Cards that were discarded during opponent''s last turn(s) are shown to the right of the card history. One pile of discarded cards are further divided into cards that were discarded from your hand (located on the left of yellow vertical line) and cards that were discarded from opponent''s hand (located on the right of yellow vertical line). Both card history and discarded cards are ordered in this fashion: last played/discarded are the leftmost.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Chat</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nYou can chat with other players in the game screen.\r\nSimply write the text in the bottom part of the game and then click the "Send message" button.\r\nFor more comfort you can use some hot keys.\r\nPush Tab (or Alt+a when your browser support keybord shortcuts) to jump into chat window, write the message and then push Tab+Enter (or Alt+s).\r\nThe message itself contains the date and time when it was written and also name of the player who wrote it.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Deck building</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n<a style="float: right;" href="img/screen_deck_building.png"><img src="img/screen_deck_building_s.png" alt="deck building section"/></a>\r\nDeck consists of 15 different cards from each group. A deck name must be different to all your other decks. Deck building section consits of control bar, where buttons that provide deck modifications and card pool modifications (filters), are located. On the left part this bar, there are filters. You can use them to filter out the unnecessary cards from the card pool. Just set the filters and then push the "Apply filters" button. On the right part of the bar, there are following buttons: Rename, Reset, Randomize and Finish. To rename deck, simply write the name in the text window and click the "Rename deck" button. If you want to empty your deck just push the "Reset" button. When you don''t want to build the deck yourself you can generate a random deck by pressing the "Randomize" button. "Finish" button will fill all remaining empty slots in your deck with random cards. Finnaly the rightmost is the average cost indicator. It shows you the average price of card per turn. Please do note that this calculation does only take into account card cost, not it''s effect. Below is your deck.  When bulding a deck, each of the 45 card slots is occupied either by some card or just with an ''Empty'' card (signalling an empty card slot). You can transfer a card from card pool by pushing Take button under the card you want to select. If you want to remove a card from your deck push the Return button under the card you whish to be removed. Any changes to the deck are immediately recorded, so it is possible to leave the deck incomplete. Such a deck cannot be used to play a game, though. When starting a game you must choose a deck from the deck list by selecting its name. There is a maximum of eight decks total for one player.\r\n</p>\r\n	\r\n<h4>New game</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nYou can start a new game in two ways.\r\nFirst, you can challenge someone to a game by selecting the challenge button in the User screen, which is in the same line as the player, who you want to challenge. The other option is to go to player''s details and challenge him from there.\r\nThen you need to choose the deck with which you want to play the game.\r\nSecond, you can wait until someone else challenges you and then accept the challenge.\r\nBefore accepting the challenge you also need to choose a deck, with which you want to play.\r\nThe player Which goes first is randomly chosen.\r\nThere is a limit of max. 15 <i>simultaneous</i> games, and only one game per opponent which you initiated (this implies that you can only have 2 parallel games against each person).\r\nUnreplied challenges in your challenge box count as games, so try to accept or reject them as soon as possible.\r\nThere is no restriction to the number of games played per day or against someone, you can play any way you like.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>When you have a game where your turn is, it is indicated by animated image ("crossed swords") in the upper part of the screen (navigation bar).</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Messages</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nIn the section "Challenges" all chellenges and messages that you recieved are located. When a new challenge/message arrives, you are informed about this in the upper menu bar with a animated image ("letter"). New messages can be written in the players section by selecting the [m] button or in the player''s details section. Also you can reply to any message by selecting the reply button.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Avatar</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nIn the settings section you can upload your own avatar. Avatar must be a jpg, jpeg, png or gif image type, must have at most 10kB and should be 60px X 60px large. If it isn''t, it will be resized to this size. Avatars with inappropriate content will be deleted and could also lead to ban.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Card terminology</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Stock - all three types of resource (Bricks, Gems, Recruits)</li>\r\n	<li>Facilities - all three types of production (Quarry, Magic, Dungeon)</li>\r\n	<li>If we are talking about Tower, Wall, Stock, Facilites ... etc. we are talking about your Tower Wall ... . Opponent''s Tower, Wall ... are addresed as Enemy tower, Enemy wall ...</li>\r\n	<li>Last card played means last card played by you not the opponent. Opponents last card played is addresed as last card played by opponent</li>\r\n	<li>Production X0, Production X2, Production X3 - you will get zero production, double production, triple production this turn</li>\r\n	<li>"Last card" means last card played or discarded by you (if more cards were played this turn then it is the most recent one)</li>\r\n	<li>"Last card played" means last card played by you (if more cards were played this turn then it is the most recent one)</li>\r\n	<li>"Last card played by opponent" means last card played by opponent (if opponent played more cards in his turn then it is the most recent one)</li>\r\n	<li>"Recently discarded" means cards discarded by you last turn or by opponent (during his last turn)</li>\r\n	<li>"Last turn" is a turn recently made by some player. Note that with the help of "Swift"/"Quick" cards, he could manage to play multiple cards in a row, thus making a multi-turn. "Last turn" refers to whole multi-turn in this case.</li>\r\n	<li>"(max N), (min N)" these are limits applied to each resource type (Bricks, Gems, Recruits). It means that you cannot get more then N of each resource for example.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Forum</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nPlease use English only at all times. Forum is divided into sections. Section contains threads - discussions about some topic. There are 3 types of threads:\r\n</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sticky - (red color) these are always at the top of the threadds list</li>\r\n	<li>Important - (orange color) these are more important then other threads</li>\r\n	<li>Normal - (white color) all other threads</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Keywords</h4>\r\n<p>\r\nKeywords represent information about the card that is too big to fit in the card box, or some property that other cards may look for while performing their effect.\r\nBelow, all keywords are listed and explained.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Alliance</b> - there is a 8% chance for each <b>Alliance</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that you will get additional Production X2.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Banish</b> - discards one random <b>Durable</b> card from enemy hand (if there is one).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Barbarian</b> - there is a 9% chance for each <b>Barbarian</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that enemy wall will be additionally lowered by ammount based on played card rarity (Common - 3 , Uncommon -  8, Rare - 15).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Brigand</b> - there is a 7% chance for each <b>Brigand</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that additional stock will be stolen from opponent (Common - 1 stock, Uncommon -  2 stock, Rare - 3 stock).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Beast</b> - there is a 8% chance for each <b>Beast</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that additional damage will be inflicted upon your enemy based on played card rarity (Common - 2 , Uncommon -  5, Rare - 10).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Burning</b> - there is a 8% chance for each <b>Burning</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that one random card from enemy hand will be discarded and bonus damage will be inflicted upon enemy tower based on played card rarity (Common - 1 dmg, Uncommon -  3 dmg, Rare - 5 dmg).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Charge</b> - when card has this keyword, it also has a number next to this keyword. When such card is played and the opponent''s wall (after the standard attack) is 0, he will receive additional damage equal to number next to charge.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Destruction</b> - it is a Destruction card.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Dragon</b> - there is a 11% chance that next card will be a rare <b>Dragon</b>. Does not apply when played card is rare.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Durable</b> - card stays on hand.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Flare attack</b> - when played, one player recieves Searing fire cards at odd card positions, while the other player recieves Searing fire cards at even card positions. Who recieves odd and who even positions is resolved randomly. The position of the played card is ignored and <b>Burning</b> cards are not replaced by Searing fires.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Holy</b> - there is a 12% chance for each <b>Holy</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that one random <b>Undead</b> card from enemy hand will be discarded and you will get additional stock based on discarded card rarity (Common - 1 stock, Uncommon -  2 stock, Rare - 3 stock).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Illusion</b> - it is a Illusion card.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Legend</b> - there is a 25% chance that one of your facilities (lowest) will be raised by one. When there are more candidates, it is resolved randomly.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Mage</b> - there is a 8% chance for each <b>Mage</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that half of the gems cost will be returned.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Nature</b> - it is a Nature card.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Quick</b> - player gets an additional turn, but no production this turn.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Rebirth</b> - when played and number of <b>Burning</b> cards in game is greater then 3, the card stays on hand and you will get additional 16 gems.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Restoration</b> - it is a Restoration card.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Skirmisher</b> - discards one random <b>Charge</b> card from enemy hand (if there is one).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Soldier</b> - there is a 8% chance for each <b>Soldier</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that half of the recruits cost will be returned.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Swift</b> - player gets additional turn, also with production.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Titan</b> - there is a 9% chance for each <b>Titan</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that next card recieved will be a <b>Titan</b>.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Undead</b> - there is a 6% chance for each <b>Undead</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that player will pay extra cost for the played card (Common - 1 stock, Uncommon -  3 stock, Rare - 5 stock).</li>\r\n	<li><b>Unliving</b> - there is a 8% chance for each <b>Unliving</b> card in hand (not counting the played one) that half of the bricks cost will be returned.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Keyboard shortcuts</h4>\r\n(might not work in some browsers without re-configuring them)\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ALT+s - send chat message</li>\r\n	<li>ALT+a - set focus to chat window</li>\r\n	<li>ALT+w - refresh button</li>\r\n	<li>ALT+q - logout</li>\r\n</ul>'),
('main', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '<p style="text-align: center">Authors (in alphabetical order): <a href="http://delo.dcs.fmph.uniba.sk/~fendek/">Mojmír Fendek</a> (Mojko) and <a href="mailto:theultramage@gmail.com">Viktor Štujber</a> (theultramage)</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Basic information</h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>Links</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The project''s location: <a href="http://arcomage.netvor.sk/">http://arcomage.netvor.sk/</a>.</li>\r\n<li>The official #arcomage channel: <a href="irc://irc.freenode.org/arcomage">irc.freenode.org</a>. Everybody''s invited!</li>\r\n<li>A powerful wiki and bug tracking system at <a href="https://netvor.sk/trac/arcomage">https://netvor.sk/trac/arcomage</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Requirements</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="http://www.w3.org/">W3C</a> standards compatible browser. We recommend <a href="http://www.mozilla.com/en-US/firefox/?from=getfirefox">Firefox</a> for basic users and <a href="http://www.opera.com/">Opera</a> for advanced users (both are free). IE 7 should also work fine, but use it only if you must.</li>\r\n<li>This site is tested and optimized for use on resolutions 800x600, 1024x768 and 1152x864. Higher resolutions (1280x1024) also work fine, lower (640x480) have problems. Full-screen mode should help in this case.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>About the game</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Arcomage is a fantasy turn-based card game. This card game simulates an epic battle between two empires including features such as constructing new buildings, training troops and decimating the enemy empire with standard attacks or sneaky tactics such as intrigue or spells. MArcomage (Multiplayer Arcomage) is its online version for two human players.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a style="float: left;" href="img/screen_deck_section.png"><img src="img/screen_deck_section_s.png" alt="deck section"/></a>\r\n<a style="float: right;" href="img/screen_game_section.png"><img src="img/screen_game_section_s.png" alt="deck section"/></a>\r\nIn order to play, a user must construct his or her own deck and challenge other players.\r\nThe battle begins as soon as the other side accepts.\r\nThere is a possibility to chat with your opponent in game.\r\n\r\nAdvantage of this game is its turn based play style.\r\nIt allows players to play as often as they like.\r\nFor example you can play few turns a day, but if you want, you can play all the time, provided you find an opponent willing to play all day as well.\r\n\r\nLets have a look at the deck building section (picture on the left).\r\nYou can see the card pool at the top of the page.\r\nBelow are filters, that you can use to select cards that interest you.\r\nAt the bottom is you deck.\r\nCards are easily added to and removed from the deck.\r\nThe game is displayed in the right picture.\r\nYou can see your cards at the top, your empire information on the middle-left.\r\nYour opponent''s cards are at the bottom and his empire information is in the middle-right.\r\nInteresting thing is, that you can see your opponent''s cards.\r\nIn the center are located cards played last turn, for both players.\r\nIn all sections there is a navigation bar at the top-most part of the screen, which allows you to change sections.\r\nFor more game information please see the Game manual.\r\n</p>'),
('modified', '2007-03-26 23:58:15', '', '<h3>Common cards</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mage guild cost lowered to 5B and 2G</li>\r\n	<li>Necromancy cost raised to 3/3/3, Banshee added to list, Play again added</li>\r\n	<li>School of nature magic cost lowered to 10B and 5G</li>\r\n	<li>School of restoration cost lowered to 7B and 4G</li>\r\n	<li>Stone gargoyle reworked, has only two modes now. Mode1: attack:12, Mode2: Enemy tower: -8</li>\r\n	<li>Stone golem cost lowered to 8B</li>\r\n	<li>Wind cost raised to 3/3/3 and Play again added</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Uncommon cards</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Academy of destruction cost lowered to 12B and 7G</li>\r\n	<li>Academy of illusion cost lowered to 14B and 9G</li>\r\n	<li>Basilisk attack reduced to 20</li>\r\n	<li>Beastiary cost reduced to 10B and 5R</li>\r\n	<li>Clay golem attack raised to 22 (in mode 1) and now raises wall by 32 (in mode 2)</li>\r\n	<li>Cursed amulet gives enemy player 10 resource of each type, when played</li>\r\n	<li>Fairy dragon cost raised to 15</li>\r\n	<li>Fallen angel attack raised to 24</li>\r\n	<li>Hectic offensive attack raised (both cases), to 30 and 13, respectively</li>\r\n	<li>Mage cost raised to 13G and Play again added</li>\r\n	<li>Sorceress cost raised to 7 and Play again added</li>\r\n	<li>Time warp cost lowered to 10G</li>\r\n	<li>Warlords keep cost lowered to 35B</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Rare cards</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Angel received Play again feature</li>\r\n	<li>Dragon golem attack rised to 50</li>\r\n	<li>Battalion of fear cost raised to 5G</li>\r\n	<li>Mana burn cost lowered to 15G</li>\r\n	<li>Necropolis now cost 10B</li>\r\n	<li>Wall shift cost lowered to 25G</li>\r\n	<li>Word of power cost lowered to 25G</li>\r\n</ul>'),
('modified', '2007-05-08 21:10:09', '', '<h3>Common cards</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Preparations - condition changed to compare dungeon insted of recruits</li>\r\n	<li>Magic well - condition changed to compare magic insted of gems</li>\r\n	<li>Mythril mine - condition changed to compare quarry insted of bricks, cost changed to 5B 5G</li>\r\n	<li>Necromancy modified it now summons <b>Undead</b> cards</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Uncommon cards</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Clay golem attack rasied to 24</li>\r\n	<li>Hectic offensive attack lowered to 25 (in the first case)</li>\r\n	<li>Thievery now steal resources according to how many <b>Brigand</b> cards you have</li>\r\n	<li>Beastiary now summons <b>Beast</b> cards and also gives wall +5</li>\r\n	<li>Enforcer attack changed - his attack is the difference between enemy recruits and enemy bricks.</li>\r\n	<li>Crypt modified it now summons <b>Undead</b> cards</li>\r\n	<li>Dragon egg modified it now summons <b>Dragon</b> cards</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Rare cards</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Residence of gods card text changed to "Instant tower victory"</li>\r\n	<li>Implosion cost raised to 35G 10G</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Keywords added to these cards:</p>\r\n<h3>Barbarian</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Amazon tribe</li>\r\n	<li>Barbarian</li>\r\n	<li>Berserker</li>\r\n	<li>Gladiator</li>\r\n	<li>Samurai</li>\r\n	<li>Highlander</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Beast</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Centaur patrol troop</li>\r\n	<li>Dire wolves</li>\r\n	<li>Giant bear</li>\r\n	<li>Minotaur</li>\r\n	<li>Werewolf</li>\r\n	<li>Basilisk</li>\r\n	<li>Giant spider</li>\r\n	<li>Griffin</li>\r\n	<li>Roc</li>\r\n	<li>Beast mistress</li>\r\n	<li>Centaur trainer</li>\r\n	<li>Crimson hawk</li>\r\n	<li>Manticore</li>\r\n	<li>White crocodile</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Brigand</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Burglars</li>\r\n	<li>Forest hunter</li>\r\n	<li>Rogue</li>\r\n	<li>Thief</li>\r\n	<li>Thieves with honor</li>\r\n	<li>Mercenaries</li>\r\n	<li>Ninja</li>\r\n	<li>Pirates</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Burning</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	